App Setup & Installation

Lecture Summary

In this lesson, we walk through the process of setting up a new React application using Vite, a fast front-end build tool. The session covers installation, dependency setup, and customization to prepare for developing an engaging landing page with animations.

  • Start by visiting Vite.dev and install the tool via npm after ensuring Node is installed.
  • Create your React app by navigating to your desired folder and using npm create vite@latest.
  • Choose React as the framework and install the necessary dependencies with npm install.
  • Modify your project by cleaning up the boilerplate files and setting up your app.jsx for customization.
  • Begin implementing key libraries such as GSAP and react-responsive for animations.
  • Ensure to register GSAP plugins like ScrollTrigger for advanced animations based on scroll position.
  • Set up Tailwind CSS for styling, making use of utility classes to simplify the design process.
  • Create a new GitHub repository and push your project regularly to keep track of changes effectively.
  • Prepare assets for the application by importing them from provided resources for use in animations.
